com.misc.common.moplaf.propagator2

Interface PropagatorFunction

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    PropagatorFunctionImpl

    public interface PropagatorFunction
extends org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject
    A representation of the model object 'PropagatorFunction'.

    Manage the refresh of derived data elements. The PropagatorFunction declares or retrieves data elements this data element depends on, remembers whether out of date, and ultimately calls methods doRefresh() or doRefresh(EObject) when the derived elements must be recalculated.

    Listening to changes is delegated to an adapter: PropagatorFunctionBindings.

    A PropagatorFunction:

    • offers two call-backs methods that may be overridden by the concrete PropagatorFunction in order to implement the refresh logic for the derived elements this adapter is responsible for; the whole purpose of the present framework is to call one of these methods exactly when needed:
      • doRefresh(), that will be called when no touching EObject has been tracked
      • doRefresh(EObject), that will be called for every touching EObject that has been tracked, if any
    • maintains its touched state
      • whether this PropagatorFunction is up to date or not: method isTouched()
        • touched = not proven up to date with respect to its direct antecedents = needs refresh
        • not touched = up to date with respects to its direct antecedents
      • a collection of touched children of this PropagatorFunction: method getTouchedChildren()
      • a collection of Notifier's responsible for the touching: method getTouchers()
    • offers a method, insuring that this Propagator become up to date: method refresh(); this entails
      • refreshing all antecedents ancestors: the parent, the parent's parent, ..., recursively
      • refreshing all antecedents siblings, antecedent's antecedents sibling, ... recursively
      • refreshing all children
      • refreshing this PropagatorFunction: method doRefresh()
    • retrieve the direct antecedents of this PropagatorFunction: the collection of PropagatorFunctions that need to be proven up to date in order to update this adapter; this collection is calculated by traversing all the inbound bindings of this PropagatorFunctionAdapter and by looking up other PropagatorFunctions (out) bound to the (in) bound features.
      • see #getAllAntecedents(): return all the direct antecedents
      • see getAntecedents(): return the direct antecedents that are siblings of this PropagatorFunctionAdapters
    • declares
      • a Parent PropagatorFunction: method doGetParent()
      • a collection of siblings PropagatorFunction it depends on: method doGetExplicitAntecedents() that do not need to be derived from the Bindings (i.e. are explicit).
      satisfying
      • first the antecedents siblings will be refreshed
      • second the children will be refreshed
      • finally this PropagatorFunction will be refreshed

    The PropagatorFunction life cycle is as follows

    • It is created by its ObjectWithPropagatorFunctions, typically when it is created, i.e. when it is owned (by method ObjectWithPropagatorFunctions.onOwned(), called by the method PropagatorFunctionAdapterManager.onNotifierContained(org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier))
    • It is enabled when the PropagatorFunctionAdapterManager is added to the scope of the propagation (method enable(), called by PropagatorFunctionAdapterManager.onAdapterAdded(org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier))
    • It is disabled when the PropagatorFunctionAdapterManager is removed from the scope of the propagation(method disable(), called by PropagatorFunctionAdapterManager.onAdapterRemoved(org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier))
    • The Parent of the a PropagatorFunction is supposed to be available when the propagator is enabled (typically when the propagator is owned), and is supposed never change. Touches are lost with ownership.
    Author:
    michel

    The following features are supported:

    • Parent
    • Antecedents
    • Antecedents Sibling
    • Touched
    • Touched Children
    • Touchers
    • Enabled
    • Object With Propagator Functions
